Remarks.
The measurements of specimens collected agree with the measurements provided by Moraes & Mesa (
1988
) for Colombian specimens, as well as with those reported by Zacarias & Moraes (
2001
) for specimens from the State of São Paulo. In contrast to what was reported by Moraes & Mesa (
1988
), and similarly to what was reported by Zacarias and Moraes (
2001
), the macroseta of tarsus IV is knob-tipped and the seta 

pd 
1

of genu I is distinctly thicker but not longer than other setae on the same segment.
